From 32500f0da9f58755dffe35d16f673d22a0fd81e3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 15:46:53 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase D (rebuild): MultiDiffEditor in Tour and Storyboard

Tour mini-diffs and Storyboard's chapter-scoped diff panel now
mount the same `KrtPrMultiDiff` instance the main Diff sub-mode
uses, scoped to the chapter's file list. Same URIs (file:// for
modified, krt-git:// for original) -> LSP and inline comments
work in those sub-modes too without any per-feature plumbing.

Tour:
  - `renderTourMiniDiffs` filters `pr.files` to the chapter's
    paths, renders the existing per-file status header strip
    (status dot, path, +/- counts) for at-a-glance scanning, then
    mounts one `KrtPrMultiDiff` below scoped to those files.
  - Strict gate matches the main sub-mode but in a compact form so
    the chapter prose / bullets / summaries keep rendering even
    when the user hasn't checked out the PR -- just the diff
    bodies fall back to a one-line CTA pointing at the Check Out
    button.

Storyboard:
  - `renderStoryboardDiffPanel` keeps the chapter file tree on the
    left, mounts a `KrtPrMultiDiff` in the right stack scoped to
    `orderedFiles`. Tree-row clicks reveal the file in the widget
    via `multiDiff.revealFile`.
  - Same strict gate as the main sub-mode (full CTA card with
    Add Workspace / Check Out hints).

`refreshCheckoutStatus` re-render path now triggers for `tour`
and `storyboard` too, so the chapter mini-diffs flip from CTA to
live diff (or back) as the working tree's HEAD changes.

CSS: `.krt-pr-tour-mini-host` (chapter-scoped widget host, shorter
than the main one -- chapters are usually a few files), and
`.krt-pr-tour-mini-cta` for the compact in-tour gate banner.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
